48:15.642 --> 48:24.751
*

48:26.153 --> 48:27.888
Louis:
Do you ever think that we --

48:27.989 --> 48:29.923
that's to say, our kind --

48:30.024 --> 48:32.359
were put on earth
for a larger purpose?

48:32.459 --> 48:37.398
*

48:37.498 --> 48:39.166
How was your night?
Fine.

48:39.266 --> 48:41.702
Jonah: So you a big-shot
businessman now.

48:41.802 --> 48:44.071
I like a little variety.

48:44.171 --> 48:45.739
The devil walks at night.

48:45.839 --> 48:46.940
*

48:47.041 --> 48:48.242
[Screams]

48:48.342 --> 48:51.378
Louis: Is my very nature
that of the devil?

48:51.478 --> 48:54.948
*

48:55.716 --> 49:01.955
*

49:02.056 --> 49:05.259
Two vampires walk into a church.
That's where we left off.

49:05.359 --> 49:08.062
Blissing out...
post priest-icide.

49:08.162 --> 49:11.398
Jones: Episode 2, "After the
Phantoms of Your Former Self" --

49:11.498 --> 49:14.468
it is Louis de Pointe du Lac
as fledgling vampire

49:14.568 --> 49:17.571
and Lestat as
his master teacher.

49:17.671 --> 49:20.241
Are you hungry, Louis?
Uh-huh.

49:20.341 --> 49:22.943
Louis trying to figure out
what this new world is,

49:23.044 --> 49:26.080
what the burdens are,
and how to use these powers.

49:26.180 --> 49:27.914
His mind is just
another bodily sound.

49:28.015 --> 49:30.384
Day and a half
since my last meal.

49:30.484 --> 49:32.453
Part of the tension here
becomes about

49:32.553 --> 49:34.321
"I am a different species
than these people."

49:34.421 --> 49:37.124
So if you're a vampire
and you're a Black man

49:37.224 --> 49:38.792
and people don't know
that you're a vampire,

49:38.892 --> 49:41.428
you are going to run up against
a couple of things.

49:41.528 --> 49:43.830
Bright and industrious,
huh?

49:43.930 --> 49:45.632
[Laughs]

49:45.732 --> 49:47.601
And you don't have to put up
with that bullshit anymore.

49:47.701 --> 49:50.304
Louis: It was both
random and unfortunate

49:50.404 --> 49:52.973
the man picked that night
to dabble in fuckery.

49:53.074 --> 49:54.308
[Snarls]

49:54.408 --> 49:56.777
But you can't be dropping bodies
left and right.

49:56.877 --> 49:58.745
What were you thinking?
He disrespected me.

49:58.845 --> 50:00.614
How did he do that?

50:00.714 --> 50:01.948
He told me
I did a good job.

50:02.049 --> 50:04.151
[Sighs] You are
a library of confusion.

50:04.251 --> 50:06.287
We get to have a little fun
with race and sexuality

50:06.387 --> 50:08.155
and then the burdens
of an interracial,

50:08.255 --> 50:09.856
interspecies relationship.

50:09.956 --> 50:11.625
You need to show restraint,
fledgling!

50:11.725 --> 50:13.527
You need to stop
using that word right now,

50:13.627 --> 50:15.296
'cause it sounded
a little like "slave."
Don't say it.

50:15.396 --> 50:16.863
Well, that's what
it fuckin' sound like.

50:16.963 --> 50:20.667
And also the professor-student
relationship. It's messy.

50:20.767 --> 50:23.204
But something about
taking of human life

50:23.304 --> 50:26.640
is not sitting well
with Louis...

50:26.740 --> 50:29.876
and the complications of trying
to have a foot in both worlds...

50:29.976 --> 50:32.313
I -- I need to go home.
...sort of reminds him

50:32.413 --> 50:34.648
of what a monster
he thinks he's become.

50:34.748 --> 50:37.518
[Both vocalizing]

50:37.618 --> 50:39.620
The killing of the tenor is,
I think,

50:39.720 --> 50:41.555
the final sort of straw
that, like,

50:41.655 --> 50:43.890
"this is never gonna be
comfortable for me."

50:43.990 --> 50:45.526
[Gasps]

50:45.626 --> 50:47.728
*

50:47.828 --> 50:50.564
"I'm never gonna be a vampire
like Lestat."

50:50.664 --> 50:53.734
Lestat: If you finally submit
to your nature,

50:53.834 --> 50:56.203
you'll see death
in all its beauty.

50:56.303 --> 50:58.205
While he is
at his most articulate

50:58.305 --> 51:00.807
about what this is about,
Louis fully admits it --

51:00.907 --> 51:02.343
"I'm not buying it."

51:02.443 --> 51:05.346
But he was still so
under the throes of Lestat,

51:05.446 --> 51:07.114
so he fakes it.

51:08.182 --> 51:10.517
Louis:
Afraid to disappoint.

51:10.617 --> 51:12.886
Jones: The idea of being
a botched vampire,

51:12.986 --> 51:16.857
that slowly begins to kind of
open up something inside Molloy.

51:16.957 --> 51:20.026
I was never going to
savor the aftertaste.

51:20.127 --> 51:22.563
I was
a shame-ridden second,

51:22.663 --> 51:26.433
a fumbling,
despondent killer.

51:26.533 --> 51:28.202
Like any good journalist,
he's sniffing around

51:28.302 --> 51:30.537
for what the armor is,
but there are things

51:30.637 --> 51:32.706
in this story where you
sit back and say,

51:32.806 --> 51:34.675
"Hmm, vampires --
they're just like us."

51:34.775 --> 51:39.946
This is the dessert I had after
I proposed to my first wife.

51:40.046 --> 51:41.415
He starts opening up
a little bit,

51:41.515 --> 51:43.750
catches himself
and turns off the interview

51:43.850 --> 51:47.053
and I think begins to, you know,
start that road down

51:47.154 --> 51:48.589
"how am I gonna
empathize against

51:48.689 --> 51:52.025
this predator
that feasts on people like me?"

51:52.125 --> 51:57.864
*

51:57.964 --> 52:03.837
*
